  <brief_summary>
    <textblock>
      The purpose of this study is to determine whether a less restrictive strategy of red blood
      cell transfusion in elderly patients following coronary bypass surgery results in enhanced
      postoperative recovery as determined by quality of life assessment, exercise tolerance and
      clinical outcomes.

      Two postoperative transfusion strategies:

        1. Liberal - transfused when Hgb is &lt;100g/L

        2. Restrictive - transfused when Hgb is &lt;70g/L
    </textblock>
  </brief_summary>
